{
  "stem": "13469.6",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It's a long story, if you read the real thing, what happened.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But basically, around about 250 people who had certificates for Palestine, they were exchanged against Germans of a certain-- Templars, I think, or [DUTCH] in Dutch.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They were a German sect of monks or religious people that lived in Jerusalem.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And 250 of those were exchanged against 250 Jews from Belsen.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And amongst those were these people, Mainz, that lived across the road from us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And after the war, we found out that all these people did actually get-- there was always a doubt that they would be just taken away somewhere else.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But they did actually go to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, we do remember their leaving, because at the last minute, somebody fell ill.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they weren't allowed to go.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they wanted replacements.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Rudi says they wanted a family of five, and that my father offered us straight away to go, but we were not accepted.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We were not sure now, because we didn't have the Palestine certificates, because I don't think we ever had them, although we'd applied for them.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And our British connections, apparently-- they didn't want-- they wanted people with Palestine certificates.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I don't think we had them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So Rudi remembers that we tried.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we nearly were on it, but we didn't.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So we do remember that particular episode, which to all those people, especially all those people with Palestine certificates-- because there were about a thousand, as we heard later-- it was a big disappointment, and to us, because at one time, we thought we might get on at the last minute.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Nevertheless, the fact that some people had apparently been exchanged-- and it was very high level people.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
